Secondary outcome measures are collected at different time point (for specific times of data collection refer to Table 4).
– Proportion of participants with Hb1Ac < 53  mmol/ mol within the two arms;
– Difference in HbA1c levels between the two arms other than at 12 months; – Reporting frequency and number of new hypoglycaemic episodes within the two arms; – Proportion of participants reaching the targeted lipid profile (LDL level < 70  mg/dl and nonHLD cholesterol level < 100  mg/dl) and BP levels (sBP < 130 mmHg or > 140 if ≥ 65 years old); – Effect on weight, lipid profile and BP levels for the App users; – Effect on physical activity performed during the last 7 days prior filling in the questionnaire, for both arm participants; – Number of hospitalisation events within the two arms; – Number of measurements and level of physical activity with the prescribed activities (body weight monitoring, BP measurements, physical activity) within the two arms; – Changes in quality of life (QoL) scores for participants of both arms; – Satisfaction and usability score of the App in the intervention arm;
